- translate ALL filenames to lowercase on DISK I/O operations (open, creat e.t.c.)
 (Initial DSI-32 tools was born on the case-insensitive system
  `cc` dos not change filename case, `as` and `ln` - required uppercase)
- emulator execulable renamed to "load" (to conform DSI-32 tools)
- renamed all source files to lowercase
- makefile: "-lrt" added for Linux
- minihelp updated
- #define debug --> #define DEBUG_LOAD
- #define TRACE_SERVICE  added
- environment: do not overflow target memory +512-4
  NOTE! CLIB seems has an error in passing 3'rd main argument: 'char **envp'
  use 'char ** environ' instead !
- added -t (timing) and -m (memory use, BUGGY!) options

